The paper focuses on the development of an autonomous racing platform using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning and neural networks in the platform also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The platform uses a monocular camera for perception, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the platform also involves distributed computing and control systems, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY).
